<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-25T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-25T20:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits 35/95a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-25T21:00:00-04:00">October 25, 1943—9
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1647. The President has stated with respect to the Argentine blocking
                            proposal (Department’s 1644, October 24, 8 p.m.) that he desires the
                            proposal tabled for the time being but reviewed every week or two.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>